'''Otto Nietzche''' (20 November 1939 - 24 April 1994) was a German politician, museum worker and soldier who served as the director of the Cologne School Board from 1965 to 1973. He is best known for his ambitious but unsuccessful attempts to run for high political offices, such as the governorship of his home state and the Chancellorship of the country. 

==Early life==
Otto was born in Cologne, Germany to jeweler Lara Klum (1905 - 1993) and hairdresser Nicholas "Nick" Nietzche (1904 - 1986). He had two siblings, Friedrich (1934 - 2007), a hairdresser like his father, and Hannah (1944 - 2023), a flight attendant. He also had a stepbrother named Liam from his mother's brief marriage to retired restaurant worker Kilian Becker (1914 - 1988). He had a pet mongrel named Marlon (1935 - 1949). 

